DeepTech深科技。
Deep Technology DeepTech.
DeepTech是一家关注新兴科技产业化的全链条内容、服务、数据和投融资平台，致力于构建一个全球科技创新合作网络。
DeepTech is a whole chain of content, services, data, and investment and financing platforms that focus on the industrialization of emerging technologies, and is committed to building a global science, technology, and innovation collaborative network.
。
.
继武汉大学中南医院利用 ECMO（叶克膜）成功救治了一名新冠患者之后，上海、甘肃都出现了用 ECMO 挽救危重病患者的案例。
Following the successful treatment of a new crown patient by ECMO in Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, ECMO has been used to rescue critically ill patients in Shanghai and Gansu.
现任台北市长、前台大医院教授柯文哲，作为将 ECMO 技术引入大中华地区的第一人曾说，“ECMO 做多了，医生会变成上帝”。
As the first person to introduce ECMO technology into Greater China, Cao Wenzhe, Taipei's mayor and a former Taichung hospital professor, once said, "If you do too much, your doctor will become God."
“当所有手段用尽仍无法维持患者生命，ECMO 可以延长生死的界限”，首都医科大学附属北京安贞医院心脏外科危重症中心主任侯晓彤说，“ECMO 不是灵丹妙药，它不能治疗病症。
"ECMO can prolong the line of life and death when all means are exhausted," said Hou Xiaodong, director of the Center for Critical Heart Surgery at Beijing Anzhen Hospital, an affiliate of the Capital Medical University.
”这个所谓 “从死神手中抢时间” 的技术，在新冠疫情中正在扮演怎样的角色？（图源：Kaiser Health News）并非所有危重病人都适用ECMO 是一种用于协助重症心肺衰竭患者进行体外呼吸循环的急救设备，全称为体外膜肺氧合，也叫“人工肺”。
What role is this so-called "snatching time from death" technique playing in the new crown epidemic? (Source: Kaiser Health News) Not all critically ill patients are treated with ECMO, an emergency device designed to help patients with severe heart-lung failure to breathe in vitro, known as extracorporeal membrane oxygenation, or "artificial lungs."
其原理是将血液从静脉中抽出，流经膜肺氧合血红蛋白并清除二氧化碳，再将经过气体交换的血液输回患者体内。
The principle is to pull blood out of the vein, flow through membrane oxygenated hemoglobin and remove carbon dioxide, and then transfer the gas-exchanged blood back to the patient.
ECMO 作为重症治疗的一项技术，本身并不是针对此次肺炎的。
ECMO itself, as a technique for severe treatment, was not targeted at pneumonia.
但新冠病毒的主要攻击对象是肺，病人通常会出现呼吸功能不全、低氧血症等等，这符合 ECMO 的适应症，所以在生命垂危的情况下，部分病人可以采用该设备进行辅助治疗。
But the main target of the new crown virus is the lung, patients often have respiratory insufficiency, hypoxemia, and so on, which is consistent with ECMO indications, so that in case of imminent death, some patients can use the device for complementary treatment.
Play视频 | ECMO 技术原理动画（来源：YouTube）中南医院急救中心副主任、急危重症移动 ECMO 中心主任夏剑在接受中新社采访时表示：“接受过 ECMO 技术诊疗的病人肺部功能受到一定程度损伤，要恢复到完全正常是不可能的，但剩下的、恢复功能的肺可以支撑平时正常功能。
Xia Jian, deputy director of the emergency center at Zhongnan Hospital and director of the ECMO emergency center at Zhongnan Hospital, said in an interview with China News Agency: "It is impossible to return to full normal lung function after ECMO treatment.
”但并不是所有危重病人都适合使用。
But not all critically ill people are fit to use.
一个前提是，只有病人在撤掉 ECMO 后肺功能可以恢复、其他器官功能也比较好的情况下才可以使用。
One premise is that lung function can be restored and other organ functions are better only if the patient removes ECMO.
而此次患病的人大多数为老年人，他们的基础病变较为严重。
But this time the person of this disease is old person mostly, their foundation pathological change is more serious.
在这种情况下，用 ECMO 的话死亡的风险会比较高。
In this case, the risk of death would be higher if ECMO were used.
中国医学科学院阜外医院体外循环中心主任吉冰洋曾表示，在使用过程中还可能发生相关的意外和并发症，包括出血、血栓、感染、肢端缺血、多器官功能衰竭等，严重者甚至危及生命。
There may also be related accidents and complications, including haemorrhage, thrombosis, infection, limb ischemia, multi-organ failure and even life-threatening conditions during use, according to the director of the Extracorporeal Circulation Center at Fuwai Hospital of the Chinese Academy of Medicine.
所以在病患选择上，没有基础病、免疫力相对强的人会被优先使用 ECMO。
Therefore, patients who do not have basic diseases and have relatively strong immunity will be given priority in ECMO use.
最大的问题是，目前应用 ECMO 抢救新冠肺炎患者的成功案例极为罕见。
The biggest problem is that successful cases of ECMO use to rescue patients with pneumonia are extremely rare.
本周一，武汉金银潭医院院长张定宇接受北美华人医生群的邀请，做了一个目前新冠病毒治疗进展的报告。
On Monday, Zhang Dingyu, director of Wuhan Gold and Silver Pool Hospital, accepted an invitation from a group of North American Chinese doctors to present a report on the progress of treatment for the new crown virus.
其中提到，危重症病人一旦上模肺 ECMO 就很少能成功拔管了，死亡率高。
It notes that once a critically ill patient has an ECMO in the upper model of the lung, the mortality rate is high.
张定宇表示，上了 ECMO 的病人仅仅听到了中南医院的彭志勇教授救活了一个病人，其他的没见到活的病人。
Zhang said patients admitted to ECMO had only heard that Professor Pang Zhiyong of Zhongnan Hospital had saved one patient, while others had not seen a living patient.
面对新冠，不具备大规模推广条件就上文提到的中南医院目前也仅有 4 台，其中 2 台是从其他医院调用的。
In the face of the new crown, not having the conditions for large-scale promotion of the above-mentioned hospital in South China is also only four, two of which are transferred from other hospitals.
武汉地区颇具实力的三甲医院中，武汉市人民医院仅有 1 台，武汉市中心医院有 2 台。
Wuhan has the strength of the Sanjia hospital, Wuhan has only one people's hospital, Wuhan central hospital has two.
因此，在资源有限的情况下，ECMO 只能应用于新冠肺炎病患中“重症中的重症患者”。
Therefore, with limited resources, ECMO can only be applied to "severe cases of severe illness" in patients with new crown pneumonia.
有数据显示，目前我国 ECMO 存量约为 400 台（不计港澳台）左右。
Data show that at present China's ECMO stock of about 400 (excluding Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan) around.
另有专家表示，2018 年统计数据显示，中国有 260 家医院可以做 ECMO，大部分是三甲医院。
Another expert said that 2018 statistics show that China has 260 hospitals can do ECMO, most of which are triple A hospitals.
相比之下，2019 年数据显示，提供 ECMO 的美国医院数量为 264 家，相差不大。
By contrast, 2019 data show that the number of United States hospitals providing ECMO is approximately 264, which is not significantly different.
图 | 武汉大学中南医院用 ECMO 治愈新型肺炎患者（来源：中南医院医生）国内很多医院想做 ECMO，但医院和医护人员的技术无法达到操作要求。
Zhongnan Hospital used ECMO to treat patients with new pneumonia. Many hospitals across the country want to become ECMO, but the skills of hospitals and health-care workers aren't up to par.
据了解，启动 ECMO 一般需要 5 人以上的专业医护团队，不同的类型需要不同的专业医护人员，包括心脏外科、体外循环、 ICU 医生护士、呼吸重症医生、急诊科医生、超声医生等等，对并发症处理、抗凝处理、如何撤机都需要技术处理和专业评估。
It is understood that starting an ECMO typically requires more than five specialist medical teams, with different types requiring different health care professionals, including cardiac surgery, cardiopulmonary bypass, ICU nurses, respiratory intensive care doctors, emergency surgeons, ultrasound doctors, etc. Technical management and professional evaluation are required for the management of complications, anticoagulation and withdrawal.
因为很多医院 ECMO 一年不到 5 例，造成专业医师稀缺，全国 260 家医院中掌握此技术的医生可能不超过 2000 人。
Because many hospitals have ECMO cases in less than five cases a year, there is a dearth of specialist physicians, and there may be no more than 2,000 doctors in 260 hospitals across the country.
此外，ECMO 还需要与多种设备配合使用，比如呼吸机、血滤机、主动脉内球囊反搏等。
In addition, ECMO also needs to be used in conjunction with a variety of devices, such as respirators, blood filters, aortic balloon retrogression, etc.
ECMO 作为高端技术设备，似乎价格很贵。
ECMO as a high-end technical equipment, seems to be very expensive.
但从机器的角度看，一台 ECMO 价格在 100 万人民币左右，在医疗器械中并不是很贵，一把超声手术刀都要三十多万。
But from a machine's point of view, an ECMO costs about RMB1 million, not very expensive in medical devices, and an ultrasound scalpel costs more than 300,000 yuan.
之所以很多人觉得“ECMO 一响，黄金千万两”，主要是因为开机所需要的离心泵头、管道和肺膜等耗材价格较贵，一套费用在 5 万到 10 万不等，一位患者的耗材可以持续使用，但每天还需要 ICU、用药、监测设备的费用 1~2 万左右。
Many people think that "ECMO ring, gold ten million two", mainly because of the power-up need for centrifugal pump head, pipe and lung film and other more expensive, a set of costs ranging from 50,000 to 100,000, a sustainable use of a patient's supplies, but the daily need for ICU, drugs, monitoring equipment costs about 10,000 to 20,000.
综合以上，在此次疫情中，短时间内大范围推广使用 ECMO 几乎难以实现。
Taken together, it is almost impossible to achieve widespread ECMO use in the short term in this epidemic.
ECMO 可以让病患的心肺暂时得到休息，原发病的治疗仍然是关键。
ECMO can let patient's heart and lungs get rest temporarily, the treatment of primary disease is still the key.
-End-参考：https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2019/06/17/end-life-decisions-questions-ecmo-can-part-life-support/1439787001/。
